headline.main: Pregnancy Prompted Closing of ‘Shuffle Along.’ Should Insurance Pay?

docs.snippet: The producers of the Broadway show are asking a court to weigh in as they seek $12 million from Lloyd’s of London....
docs.abstract: Producers of Broadway musical Shuffle Along, which closed prematurely after star Audra McDonald became pregnant, file suit against insurance company Lloyd’s of London, which has denied damages claims based on argument that pregnancy was neither 'accident' nor 'illness.'
docs.lead_paragraph: The producers of the Broadway show are asking a court to weigh in as they seek $12 million from Lloyd’s of London.
